cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.NA 

The paper deals with supervised classification and feature selection, which are topics commonly studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of an 1 norm for the constraint and loss function is also a common technique in sparse optimization (cs.DS). The datasets used in the experiments are from biological data, which suggests a possible connection to bioinformatics (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a novel constrained primal-dual method for optimization, which falls under numerical analysis (cs.NA).
